        Official Singles Chart on 24/7/2020

        24 July 2020 - 30 July 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        I’m a bit pushed for time to do a full review today, so instead, here’s a Traffic Light System for this week’s Top 40…

        🔴 (Negative):

        1) The two new DJ Khaled songs are the two highest debuts of the week! His production is incredibly basic on both tracks, but my concern with Drake, who sounds absolutely terrible due to his whiny delivery.

        2) ‘On Deck’ isn’t that good either sadly! My issue isn’t really with Abra Cadabra flow, but the deep & swampy production drowns out anything he says. Seriously, all I could understand from him was “jiggy-jiggy”!

        3) Joy Division completely missed the Top 40! Not surprised though, given that a majority of their sales came from vinyl. Still would’ve been cool seeing them here though!

        4) ‘Don’t Need Love’ hit ACR, causing it to crash out of the Top 40 completely!

        5) ‘This City’ didn’t do anywhere near as well as either update was indicating! Oh well, at least it didn’t fall back.

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Savage Love’ falls from the top spot! Honestly, while I predicted a while back that this would be the Song Of The Summer, I actually hope I’m proven wrong! I still like it more than most regulars here, but it’s one of those hits that’s getting old fast thanks to extreme overplay.

        2) ‘Watermelon Sugar’ rises to a new peak of #5. It’s still not bad by any means, but I can’t escape it, haha!

        3) ‘Who’s That What’s That’ is back in the Top 40! The hype has kind of faded for me, but hey, congratulations to Niko B for getting his debut song onto NOW! 106.

        4) ‘Dior’ also comes back! The song has grown on me a little & I appreciate how hard Pop Smoke goes in this, but that bubbly bass beat has still not been able to win me over.

        5) Drake did at least redeem himself this week with his feature on ‘Only You Freestyle’ alongside Headie One! Looking at the huge streaming numbers, I wouldn’t rule out a climb to #1 for this next week (although a midweek release might hold it back).

        6) ‘Breaking Me’ is on ACR! It actually dropped less than expected & while it’s cool that the song became massive across Europe, it’s time to move on from it now.

        7) ‘Blinding Lights’ has dropped back a bit from where it was a few days ago. I can’t really complain too much though, given it’s longevity!

        8) Woah… where did ‘Go Crazy’ come from?! I like Chris Brown’s part, but Young Thug’s is just okay.

        🟢 (Positive):

        1) Obviously the best news of the week is that Joel Corry & MNEK are #1!!! I generally think the quality of the chart-toppers in 2020 are okay, but this one is head & shoulders above them all… or should I say “Head & Heart” above them all, haha.

        2) ‘Rain On Me’ is still sticking around in the Top 5!!!

        3) AJ Tracey has two songs in the Top 10 (‘West Ten’ & ‘Dinner Guest’) for another week!

        4) ‘Heaven On My Mind’ keeps moving up! I think it’s going to be a future Top 20 hit, probably either next week or the following one.

        5) ‘Fake Friends’ climbed nine places almost into the Top 30! Honestly, if clubs were open right now, this song would be played everywhere. Let’s keep the momentum for it going!

        6) ‘What’s Love Got To Do With It’ just sneaks into the Top 40! Obviously, it doesn’t top the original, but Kygo has proved for a second time that he can effectively remake 80’s disco classics.

        7) Not related to the singles chart as such, but Ellie Goulding is back with a #1 album with ‘Brighter Blue’. It’s her first studio album in five years & I really wish she got some successful tracks from it!

        8) Speaking of albums, Taylor Swift has gone indie-folk on us & I’m all for it! I’ll post my ratings of each track on the album in a few minutes.
